topic.p:
The received advice is integrated in the system. 
Thus, you can read it any time. You can get advice on the following vital subjects*:


Legislation on accounting and reporting;

Legislation on taxes;

Labour legislation;

Civil legislation regulating relations in the sphere of entrepreneurial activities.

You enjoy the guarantee of getting advice as soon as possible
When the issue is accepted for processing,* you will get a notification with a preliminary suggestion of the time of reply;
The most intricate issues require not more than two days.

 GARANT System Platform F1 may be supplied in the following options:

 Installation network
	(multiple-user or single-user)
 client server;

 Installation network
	(multiple-user or single-user)
 file server;

 Installation local option; 

 Single-user network or local disk (DVD); 
Below are the common requirements for all types of supplied options, as well as the special requirements to the network server options.

An important feature of the Basic Search is dependence on the content of the Main Window of the program. This permits to solve the following tasks with the help of the Basic Search:

Searching through the whole databank;

Searching in the document list;

Context search in the document names of the list;

Searching the text of the opened document.

Enter one or several words separated with spaces. The search will select documents, matching your request that contain simultaneously all words mentioned by you.
At your request there will be found documents containing the exact coincidence with the word indicated by you.
To find all the words beginning with the letters entered by you, put an asterisk <*> at the end. For example, having entered "tax", you will find the documents containing the words "taxes", "taxation", "taxable" and others.
In the search field it is also possible to enter phrases arranging the words in any order, for example, 'filling out a tax declaration', 'tax declaration filling out' etc.
The entry field may be used to enter letters, figures, space < >, hyphen <-> and inverted commas <"">;
exclamation mark <!> and the asterisk <*> may be used only at the end of the word, i.e. all characters entered after them to the space will be ignored;
symbols </>, <.>, may be used only to separate digits;
other symbols may not be used in the Basic Search.
Judicial and arbitration > practices
See recommendations on the filling of the context fields.

ol.li:
The advice is provided in the four main subjects:

Legislation on accounting and reporting;

Legislation on taxes;

Labour legislation;

Civil legislation regulating relations in the entrepreneurial sphere.

In the framework of the following subjects, the following issues are covered:

application of the actual legislation;

current changes in the legislation;

particular legal issue.

Advice is not provided in the following issues:

financial analysis of economic operations;

legal expert evaluation of contracts and other documents;

working out draft contracts;

legal support in the cases of tax checks;

assessment of judicial prospects of disputes;

accounting particulars of credit and budget-supported organisations.

